# Quality Assurance

## Architecture Understanding
- Load and parse complete Mermaid diagrams in docs/architecture.mermaid
- Extract and understand:
  - Module boundaries and relationships
  - Data flow patterns
  - System interfaces
  - Component dependencies
- Validate any changes against architectural constraints
- Ensure new code maintains defined separation of concerns

## Error Prevention
- Verify type consistency
- Check for potential null/undefined
- Validate against business rules
- Ensure error handling
- Implement logging for errors
- Add transaction handling for database operations
- Test edge cases
- Validate user inputs

## Documentation Requirements
- Update README.md for major feature additions
- Maintain comprehensive API documentation
- Document all management commands
- Create usage examples for new features
- Update status.md for completed work
- Add technical documentation for architectural changes
- Document test procedures

## Git Workflow
- Commit changes with descriptive messages
- Update documentation before pushing
- Verify all tests pass before pushing
- Follow conventional commit message format when possible
- Push changes only after updating all required documentation